                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>", top right column and bottom five lines: excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3575Mashaf"/>, from section Kwullomu
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso)"/>", top left 13 lines: Hymns to the Saints.
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለክሙ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ተሐፅነ፡ በሀሊበ፡ ወንጌል፡ ሐዲስ፡ አባ፡ ዮሐኒ፡ ወጻድቅ፡ ኪሮስ፡...</foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ivr(ecto)"/> Story of the teaching of the Lord’s Prayer
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                        ይቤሉ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ መሐረነ፡ ጸሎተ፡ በከመ፡ መሐረ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ለአርዳIሁ፡...
                        አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት፡ ብሂል፡ በእንተ፡ ዘተወለድነ፡ እምኔሁ፡ በዳግም፡ ልደት፡ እማይ፡ ወእመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡...
                      </foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a04">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#111v"/>, marginal note: inserted Psalm of the Virgin
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a05">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#140r"/>, marginal note: inserted Psalm of the Virgin
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a06">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#180r"/>, note in red ink: Days of the year that the heavens are open to receive prayers, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኅወ፡ ሰማይ፡</foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a07">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#180r"/>, column 2: List of the Feast Days of the Apostles.
                      The text in this manuscript is a good representative:
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠረቀ፡ መስከረም፡ አመ፡ ፩፡ በርተሎሜዎስ፡ ሐዋርያ፡፡ ሠረቀ፡ ጥቅምት፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፪፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ሐዋርያ፡...</foreign>
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>", top three lines: Pen trials and scrawl
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a08">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#r(ecto)"/>", bottom two lines (in blue ink): note of ownership, insufficiently legible
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a09">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>", top left column: note of ownership, Kǝflä Giyorgis and his son Gäbrä Mika’el
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a10">
                      <desc type="Genealogy">
                      <locus target="#iiiv(erso)"/>", col. 1, lower–column 2: Genealogy of a family
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#78r"/>: Three cross-shaped symbols stand in the margins of the text, one in the gutter margin and two in the fore edge margin to mark the midpoint of the psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a11">
                      <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">
                      <locus target="#158r"/>, lines 5ff:
                      Colophon: “This book belongs to Aminä Krestos, commissioned by his wealth, on year 7227 AM, (= 1734/5), second month, third day of month of Ḫǝdar,
                      completed on Wednesday at noontime, on the year of Luke (the Evangelist), in the third year and twenty-first day of the reign of Iyyasu (II),
                      son of Bäkkaffa, two months (lit. moons), eleven nights, 24 Mäṭqǝ‘ǝ and seven Abäqte. I, Joseph, your servant, sinner and wretch,
                      wrote this so that you can read this book. Say for me one Our Father and one Hail Mary.”
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a12">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#180v"/>, column 1: note of ownership, Däbtära Kǝfle
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      EMML numbers are visible throughout the manuscript
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 1–2
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e05">
                      <desc>
                        In Psalm 118, the sections are numbered. There is a corresponding set of lines for the Virgin. The spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters are also present
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e06">
                      <desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24v #26v #42v #58v #62r"/>, etc.);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#35v #55v #65r #66v"/>, etc.);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#139r"/>, line 2; <locus target="#172v"/>, col. 1, line 6; <locus target="#173r"/>, col. 2, line 10), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#178r"/>, col. 1, line 1);
                        erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#70r"/>);
                        text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#9v #24r #33v"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e07">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                        Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                        appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate
                        script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                        completes the line of text above or below the end of the line
                        (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of
                        lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#4v #8v #15r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

